A work group of the State Council, China's cabinet, will leave here on Friday afternoon for Harbin, capital of northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, to investigate the major water pollution in Songhua River, which has led to a fourday water supply suspension in the city.
At a press conference held here on Thursday, a senior SEPA official said a chemical plant of the Jilin Petrochemical Company under China National Petroleum Corp. should be held responsible for the pollution of the Songhua River.
